The principal of a primary school in Finetown, Johannesburg, was gunned down early on Friday. Provincial education department spokesperson Steve Mabona said the principal  was killed inside the school premises. “We are  on our way to the school to understand what might have transpired there,” said Mabona. Gauteng police spokesperson Capt Kay Makhubele confirmed  the principal had been shot several times. A murder case has been opened. No arrests have been made yet. This is a developing story. TimesLIVE